        git shortlog -w78,0,8 --format="\%h \%s"

s-roff, 2014-08-19
------------------

S-roff has been forked from GNU troff, revision 1.19.2-574-gecbf4f1
(from the official GNU troff git(1) repository; the last commit that
is still licensed under GPLv2).

Appendix
^^^^^^^^

The complete changelog of commits in between two versions OLD and
NEW can be inspected by using the git(1) `log' command:

  $ git log --reverse --topo-order --abbrev-commit OLD..NEW
  # Only topic branch headers (--no-merges for content commits only):
  $ git log --oneline --reverse --topo-order --merges OLD..NEW
  # Same, but truly accessible:
  $ git log --oneline --reverse --topo-order --merges --parents OLD..NEW |
    while read c1 c2 c3 c4 c5 c6; do
      printf "%-24s: \$ git log --oneline --no-merges %s ^%s\n" \
        "${c6}" "${c1}" "${c2}";
    done

Entries for releases before v0.0.0 have been cut off and can be
found in the git(1) repository.

  pre 0.0.0         : $ git show s-roff:ChangeLog{,.{115,116,117,118}}

The post 0.0.0 are also accessible via HTTPS?, just replace X.Y.Z
accordingly:

  \https?://git.sdaoden.eu/cgit/s-roff.git/tree/NEWS?h=vX.Y.Y

For even older, i.e., GNU releases you need to look at the ChangeLog
files under the [s-roff] tag, i.e.,

  $ git show s-roff:ChangeLog{,.{115,116,117,118}}

